Learner's submission: {{ $('When Called by Supervisor').item.json.text }}
Learner Slack username: {{ $('When Called by Supervisor').item.json.user_name }}

Evaluate the submission against the module content. Decide:
- PASS: The learner demonstrated understanding of the module objectives
- FAIL: The submission does not meet the requirements, explain what is missing
- INCOMPLETE: The submission is too brief or off-topic

Respond with a JSON object:
{
  "result": "PASS" | "FAIL" | "INCOMPLETE",
  "feedback": "<encouraging, specific feedback in 2-3 sentences>",
  "score": <0-100>
}

parameters.jsCode:
const raw = $json.output || $json.text || '{}';
let parsed;
try {
  const match = raw.match(/\{[\s\S]*\}/);
  parsed = JSON.parse(match ? match[0] : raw);
} catch (e) {
  parsed = { result: 'INCOMPLETE', feedback: raw, score: 0 };
}
return [{ json: { ...parsed, ...$('Get Current Module').item.json, ...$('When Called by Supervisor').item.json } }];

